obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5020)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5020&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Recovery`
  line `of Debts ^1[and Bankruptcy] Act, 1993.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir^*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 24th day of June, 1993.`
  line
  line `(4) ^2[Save as otherwise provided, the provisions of this Code] Act shall not apply where the amount of debt due to any bank or`
  line `financial institution or to a consortium of banks or financial institutions is less than ten lakh rupees or`
  line `such other amount, being not less than one lakh rupees, as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line specify.
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule, for "Due to Banks and Financial Institutions" (w.e.f. 1-12-2019) .`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `2.Subs, by s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule, ibid for "The provision of this Code" (w.e.f. 1-12-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5021)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5021&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) Appellate Tribunal means an Appellate Tribunal established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) application means an application made to a Tribunal under section 19;`
  line
  line `(c) appointed day, in relation to a Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal, means the date on which`
  line `such Tribunal is established under sub-section (1) of section 3 or, as the case may be, sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) bank means`
  line
  line `(i) banking company;`
  line
  line `(ii) a corresponding new bank;`
  line
  line `(iii) State Bank of India;`
  line
  line `(iv) a subsidiary bank; or`
  line
  line `(v) a Regional Rural Bank;`
  line
  line `^1[(vi) a multi-State co-operative bank;]`
  line
  line `(e) banking company shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (c) of section 5 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `^2[(ea) Chairperson means a Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal appointed under section 9;]`
  line
  line `(f) corresponding new bank shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (da) of section 5 of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `^3[(g) debt means any liability (inclusive of interest) which is claimed as due from any person ^4[or a pooled investment vehicle as defined in clause (da) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956)] by`
  line `a bank or a financial institution or by a consortium of banks or financial institutions during the course`
  line `of any business activity undertaken by the bank or the financial institution or the consortium under`
  line `any law for the time being in force, in cash or otherwise, whether secured or unsecured, or assigned,`
  line `or whether payable under a decree or order of any civil court or any arbitration award or otherwise or`
  line `under a mortgage and subsisting on, and legally recoverable on, the date of the application ^5[and`
  line `includes any liability towards debt securities which remains unpaid in full or part after notice of`
  line `ninety days served upon the borrower by the debenture trustee or any other authority in whose favour`
  line `security interest is created for the benefit of holders of debt securities or;]]`
  line
  line `^6[(ga) debt securities means debt securities listed in accordance with regulations made by the`
  line `Securities Exchange Board of India under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992`
  line `(15 of 1992);]`
  line
  line `(h) financial institution means--`
  line
  line `(i) a public financial institution within the meaning of section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `^7[(ia) the securitisation company or reconstruction company which has obtained a certificate`
  line `of registration under sub-section (4) of section 3 of the Securitisation and Reconstruction of`
  line `Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002);]`
  line
  line `^8[(ib) a debenture trustee registered with the Board and appointed for secured debt securities;]`
  line
  line `(ii) such other institution as the Central Government may, having regard to its business`
  line `activity and the area of its operation in India, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `^9[(ha) financial lease means a lease under a lease agreement of tangible asset, other than`
  line `negotiable instrument or negotiable document, for transfer of lessor's right therein to the lessee for a`
  line `certain time in consideration of payment of agreed amount periodically and where lessee becomes the`
  line `owner of the such assets at the expiry of the term of lease or on payment of the agreed residual`
  line `amount, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(i) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(j) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^10[(ja) Presiding Officer means the Presiding Officer of the Debts Recovery Tribunal appointed`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4;]`
  line
  line `^11[(jb) property means--`
  line
  line `(a) immovable property;`
  line
  line `(b) movable property;`
  line
  line `(c) any debt or any right to receive payment of money, whether secured or unsecured;`
  line
  line `(d) receivables, whether existing or future;`
  line
  line `(e) intangible assets, being know-how, patent, copyright, trade mark, licence, franchise or`
  line `any other business or commercial right of similar nature, as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with Reserve Bank;]`
  line
  line `(k) Recovery Officer means a Recovery Officer appointed by the Central Government for each`
  line `Tribunal under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(l) Regional Rural Bank means a Regional Rural Bank established under section 3 of the`
  line `Regional Rural Banks Act, 1976 (21 of 1976);`
  line
  line `^12[(la) secured creditor shall have the meaning as assigned to it in clause (zd) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2 of the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security`
  line `Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002);`
  line
  line `(lb) security interest means mortgage, charge, hypothecation, assignment or any other right,`
  line `title or interest of any kind whatsoever upon property, created in favour of any bank or financial`
  line `institution and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) such right, title or interest upon tangible asset, retained by the bank or financial institution`
  line `as owner of the property, given on hire or financial lease or conditional sale which secures the`
  line `obligation to pay any unpaid portion of the purchase price of the asset or an obligation incurred or`
  line `any credit provided to enable the borrower to acquire the tangible asset; or`
  line
  line `(b) such right, title or interest in any intangible asset or licence of any intangible asset, which`
  line `secures the obligation to pay any unpaid portion of the purchase price of the intangible asset or`
  line `the obligation incurred or any credit extended to enable the borrower to acquire the intangible`
  line `asset or licence of intangible asset;]`
  line
  line `(m) State Bank of India means the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(n) subsidiary bank shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (k) of section 2 of the State`
  line `Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959);`
  line
  line `(o) Tribunal means the Tribunal established under sub-section (1) of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 12 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (g) (w.e.f 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 160 (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 19 (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `7 Ins. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5022)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1-12-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5022&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, establish one or`
  line `more Tribunals, to be known as the Debts Recovery Tribunal, to exercise the jurisdiction, powers and`
  line `authority conferred on such Tribunal by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A)The Central Government shall by notification establish such number of Debts Recovery`
  line `Tribunals and its benches as it may consider necessary, to exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority`
  line `of the Adjudicating Authority conferred on such Tribunal by or under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy`
  line `Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall also specify, in the notification referred to in sub-section (1), the`
  line `areas within which the Tribunal may exercise jurisdiction for entertaining and deciding the applications`
  line `filed before it.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5023)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 27, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5023&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Tribunal shall consist of one person only (hereinafter referred`
  line `to as the Presiding Officer) to be appointed, by notification, by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) authorise the Presiding Officer of any other Tribunal established under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force to discharge the function of the Presiding Officer of a Debt Recovery Tribunal`
  line `under this Act in addition to his being the Presiding Officer of that Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) authorise the judicial Member holding post as such in any other Tribunal, established under`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, to discharge the functions of the Presiding Officer of Debts`
  line `Recovery Tribunal under this Act, in addition to his being the judicial Member of that Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5024)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Presiding Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5024&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified for`
  line `appointment as the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal unless he is, or has been, or is qualified to be, a`
  line `District Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5025)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of Presiding Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for section 6 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5025&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Term of office of Presiding Officer.-- The Presiding Officer of a Tribunal shall hold office for`
  line `a term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office and shall be eligible for`
  line `reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall hold office as the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal after he has attained`
  line `the age of sixty-five years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (5026)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5026&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officer. -- Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of office, salaries and allowances,`
  line `resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the Presiding Officer of the Tribunal`
  line `appointed after the commencement of ^2[the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Presiding Officer appointed before the commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI`
  line `of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Act, and the`
  line `rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had not come into`
  line force.]
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 179 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 18, for “Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall be governed by the provisions of section 184 of that Act” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5027)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Staff of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5027&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall provide the Tribunal ^1[with one or more`
  line `Recovery Officers] and such other officers and employees as that Government may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[The Recovery Officers] and other officers and employees of a Tribunal shall discharge their`
  line `functions under the general superintendence of the Presiding Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the ^3[Recovery Officers] and other`
  line `officers and employees of a Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 4, for "with a Recovery Officer" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "The Recovery Officer" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "Recovery Officer" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5028)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Establishment of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5028&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `establish one or more Appellate Tribunals, to be known as the Debts Recovery Appellate Tribunal, to`
  line `exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on such Tribunal by or under this Act:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Central Government may authorise the Chairperson of any other Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, established under any other law for the time being in force, to discharge the functions of the`
  line `Chairperson of the Debts Recovery Appellate Tribunal under this Act in addition to his being the`
  line `Chairperson of that Appellate Tribunal.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) The Central Government shall, by notification, establish such number of Debt Recovery`
  line `Appellate Tribunals to exercise jurisdiction, powers and authority to entertain appeal against the order`
  line `made by the Adjudicating Authority under Part III of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016`
  line `(31 of 2016).]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall also specify in the notification, referred to in sub-section (1) the`
  line `Tribunals in relation to which the Appellate Tribunal may exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the Central Government may`
  line `authorise the Chairperson of one Appellate Tribunal to discharge also the functions of the Chairperson of`
  line `other Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1-12-2019).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 5 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5029)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Composition of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Presiding Officer of the Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5029&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `An Appellate Tribunal shall consist of one person only`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as ^1[the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal]) to be appointed, by notification,`
  line `by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5030)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5030&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `10. Qualifications for appointment as ^1[the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal].-- A person`
  line `shall not be qualified for appointment as ^2[the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal] unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, or is qualified to be, a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade I of that service`
  line `for at least three years; or`
  line
  line `(c) has held office as the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal for at least three years.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Presiding Officer of the Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5031)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Term of office of Chairperson of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 30, for section 11 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5031&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Term of office of Chairperson of Appellate Tribunal.-- The Chairperson of an Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall hold office for a term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office and`
  line `shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall hold office as the Chairperson of a Appellate Tribunal after he has`
  line `attained the age of seventy years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5032)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Staff of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5032&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 7 (except those relating to Recovery`
  line `Officer) shall, so far as may be, apply to an Appellate Tribunal as they apply to a Tribunal and`
  line `accordingly references in that section to "Tribunal" shall be construed as references to "Appellate`
  line `Tribunal" and references to "Recovery Officer" shall be deemed to have been omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5033)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5033&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line The
  line `salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service (including pension,`
  line `gratuity and other retirement benefits) of, ^1[the Presiding Officer] of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an`
  line `Appellate Tribunal] shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of ^2[the`
  line `Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal shall be varied to his]`
  line `disadvantage after appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 2, for "the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "the said Presiding Officers shall be varied to their" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5034)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Filling up of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5034&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If, for any reason other than temporary absence, any vacancy occurs in`
  line `the office of ^1[the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal], then the`
  line `Central Government shall appoint another person in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill the`
  line `vacancy and the proceedings may be continued before the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal from the`
  line `stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5035)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5035&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[The Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an`
  line `Appellate Tribunal] may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign`
  line `his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^2[the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal] shall,`
  line `shall, unless he is permitted by the Central Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold`
  line `office until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly`
  line `appointed as his successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the`
  line earliest.
  line
  line `(2) ^1[The Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal] shall not be`
  line `removed from his office except by an order made by the Central Government on the ground of proved`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity after inquiry,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal, made by a Judge of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of ^3[the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal], made by a Judge of the Supreme`
  line Court,
  line `in which ^4[the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal] has been`
  line `informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of these`
  line `charges:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the Central Government, during the pendency of the inquiry against the Presiding`
  line `Officer or a Chairperson, as the case may be, may, after consulting the Chairperson of the Selection`
  line `Committee constituted for selection of Presiding Officer or Chairperson, pass an order suspending the`
  line `Presiding Officer or the Chairperson, if it is satisfied that he should cease to discharge his functions as a`
  line `Presiding Officer or Chairperson, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by rules, regulate the procedure for the investigation of`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity of ^6[the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an Appellate`
  line Tribunal.]
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 2, for the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for the said Presiding Officer (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Presiding Officer of an Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "the Presiding Officer concerned" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `6 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 7, for "the aforesaid Presiding Officer" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (5036)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 17
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5036&sectionno=15A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson.-- Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and the`
  line `terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson of the Appellate Tribunal appointed after the commencement of`
  line `^2[the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson appointed before the commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance`
  line `Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Act, and the rules made thereunder as`
  line `if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had not come into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 179 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 18, for Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall be governed by the provisions of section 184 of that Act (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5037)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Orders constituting Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal to be final and not to invalidate its proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 2, for "the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5037&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No order of the Central Government appointing any person as ^1[the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal`
  line `or the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal] shall be called in question in any manner, and no act or proceeding`
  line `before a Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal shall be called in question in any manner on the ground merely of any`
  line `defect in the constitution of a Tribunal or an Appellate Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5038)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Jurisdiction, powers and authority of Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5038&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Tribunal shall exercise, on and from the`
  line `appointed day, the jurisdiction, powers and authority to entertain and decide applications from the banks and`
  line `financial institutions for recovery of debts due to such banks and financial institutions.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Without prejudice to sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(a) the Tribunal shall exercise, on and from the date to be appointed by the Central Government, the`
  line `jurisdiction, powers and authority to entertain and decide applications under Part III of Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).`
  line
  line `(b) the Tribunal shall have circuit sittings in all district headquarters.]`
  line
  line `(2) An Appellate Tribunal shall exercise, on and from the appointed day, the jurisdiction, powers and authority`
  line `to entertain appeals against any order made, or deemed to have been made, by a Tribunal under this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Without prejudice to sub-section (2), the Appellate Tribunal shall exercise, on and from the date to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government, the jurisdiction, powers and authority to entertain appeals against the order`
  line `made by the Adjudicating Authority under Part III of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)).]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1-12-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1-12-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (5039)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of Chairperson of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5039&sectionno=17A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Power of Chairperson of Appellate Tribunal.-- (1) The Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `exercise general power of superintendence and control over the Tribunals under his jurisdiction including the power`
  line `of appraising the work and recording the annual confidential reports of Presiding Officers.`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) For the purpose of exercise of general powers of superintendence and control over Tribunals under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Chairperson may--`
  line
  line `(i) direct the Tribunals to furnish, in such form, at such intervals and within such time, information relating`
  line `to pending cases both under this Act and the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and`
  line `Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002), or under any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `number of cases disposed of, number of new cases filed and such other information as may be considered`
  line `necessary by the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(ii) convene meetings of the Presiding Officers of Tribunals periodically to review their performance.`
  line
  line `(1B) Where on assessment of the performance of any Presiding Officer of the Tribunal or otherwise, the`
  line `Chairperson is of the opinion that an inquiry is required to be initiated against such Presiding Officer for`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity, he shall submit a report to the Central Government recommending action against such`
  line `Presiding Officer, if any, under section 15, and for reasons to be recorded in writing for the same.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal having jurisdiction over the Tribunals may, on the`
  line `application of any of the parties or on his own motion after notice to the parties and after hearing them,`
  line `transfer any case from one Tribunal for disposal to any other Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 8 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016)`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5040)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5040&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, no court or other authority shall have, or`
  line `be entitled to exercise, any jurisdiction, powers or authority (except the Supreme Court, and a High Court`
  line `exercising jurisdiction under articles 226 and 227 of the Constitution) in relation to the matters specified`
  line `in section 17:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that any proceedings in relation to the recovery of debts due to any multi-State`
  line `co-operative bank pending before the date of commencement of the Enforcement of Security Interest and`
  line `Recovery of Debts Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 (1 of 2013) under the Multi-State Co-operative`
  line `Societies Act, 2002 (39 of 2002) shall be continued and nothing contained in this section shall, after such`
  line `commencement, apply to such proceedings.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5041)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `Application to the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5041&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Application to the Tribunal.-- (1) Where a bank or a financial institution has to recover any`
  line `debt from any person, it may make an application to the Tribunal within the local limits of whose`
  line jurisdiction
  line
  line `^2[(a) the branch or any other office of the bank or financial institution is maintaining an account`
  line `in which debt claimed is outstanding, for the time being; or]`
  line
  line `^3[(aa)] the defendant, or each of the defendants where there are more than one, at the time of`
  line `making the application, actually and voluntarily resides, or carries on business, or personally works`
  line `for gain; or`
  line
  line `(b) any of the defendants, where there are more than one, at the time of making the application,`
  line `actually and voluntarily resides, or carries on business, or personally works for gain; or`
  line
  line `(c) the cause of action, wholly or in part, arises:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the bank or financial institution may, with the permission of the Debts Recovery`
  line `Tribunal, on an application made by it, withdraw the application, whether made before or after the`
  line `Enforcement of Security Interest and Recovery of Debts Laws (Amendment) Act, 2004 (30 of 2004) for`
  line `the purpose of taking action under the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and`
  line `Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002), if no such action had been taken earlier under`
  line `that Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any application made under the first proviso for seeking permission from the`
  line `Debts Recovery Tribunal to withdraw the application made under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by it`
  line `as expeditiously as possible and disposed of within thirty days from the date of such application:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case the Debts Recovery Tribunal refuses to grant permission for withdrawal of`
  line `the application filed under this sub-section, it shall pass such orders after recording the reasons therefor.]`
  line
  line `^5[(1A) Every bank being, multi-State co-operative bank referred to in sub-clause (vi) of clause (d) of`
  line `section 2, may, at its option, opt to initiate proceedings under the Multi-State Co-operative Societies Act,`
  line `2002 (39 of 2002) to recover debts, whether due before or after the date of commencement of the`
  line `Enforcement of the Security Interest and Recovery of Debts Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 (1 of 2013)`
  line `from any person instead of making an application under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(1B) In case, a bank being, multi-State co-operative bank referred to in sub-clause (vi) of clause (d) of`
  line `section 2 has filed an application under this Chapter and subsequently opts to withdraw the application for`
  line `the purpose of initiating proceeding under the Multi-State Co-operative Societies Act, 2002 (39 of 2002)`
  line `to recover debts, it may do so with the permission of the Tribunal and every such application seeking`
  line `permission from the Tribunal to withdraw the application made under sub-section (1A) shall be dealt with`
  line `by it as expeditiously as possible and disposed of within thirty days from the date of such application:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the Tribunal refuses to grant permission for withdrawal of the application filed`
  line `under this sub-section, it shall pass such orders after recording the reasons therefor.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where a bank or a financial institution, which has to recover its debt from any person, has filed an`
  line `application to the Tribunal under sub-section (1) and against the same person another bank or financial`
  line `institution also has claim to recover its debt, then, the later bank or financial institution may join the`
  line `applicant bank or financial institution at any stage of the proceedings, before the final order is passed, by`
  line `making an application to that Tribunal.`
  line
  line `^6[(3) Every application under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be in such form, and shall be`
  line `accompanied with true copies of all documents relied on in support of the claim along with such fee, as`
  line `may be prescribed:]`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee may be prescribed having regard to the amount of debt to be recovered:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section relating to fee shall apply to cases`
  line `transferred to the Tribunal under sub-section (1) of section 31.`
  line
  line `^7[Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section, documents includes statement of account or any`
  line `entry in bankers book duly certified under the Bankers Books Evidence Act, 1891 (18 of 1891).]`
  line
  line `^8[(3A) Every applicant in the application filed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) for recovery of`
  line `debt, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) state particulars of the debt secured by security interest over properties or assets belonging to`
  line `any of the defendants and the estimated value of such securities;`
  line
  line `(b) if the estimated value of securities is not sufficient to satisfy the debt claimed, state particulars`
  line `of any other properties or assets owned by any of the defendants, if any; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the estimated value of such other assets is not sufficient to recover the debt, seek an order`
  line `directing the defendant to disclose to the Tribunal particulars of other properties or assets owned by`
  line `the defendants.]`
  line
  line `^9[^10[(3B)] If any application filed before the Tribunal for recovery of any debt is settled prior to the`
  line `commencement of the hearing before that Tribunal or at any stage of the proceedings before the final`
  line `order is passed, the applicant may be granted refund to the fees paid by him at such rates as may be`
  line prescribed.]
  line
  line `^11[(4) On receipt of application under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the Tribunal shall issue`
  line `summons with following directions to the defendant--`
  line
  line `(i) to show cause within thirty days of the service of summons as to why relief prayed for should`
  line `not be granted;`
  line
  line `(ii) direct the defendant to disclose particulars of properties or assets other than properties and`
  line `assets specified by the applicant under clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (3A); and`
  line
  line `(iii) to restrain the defendant from dealing with or disposing of such assets and properties`
  line `disclosed under clause (c) of sub-section (3A) pending the hearing and disposal of the application for`
  line `attachment of properties.]`
  line
  line `^12[(4A) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 65A of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882`
  line `(4 of 1882), the defendant, on service of summons, shall not transfer by way of sale, lease or otherwise`
  line `except in the ordinary course of his business any of the assets over which security interest is created and`
  line `other properties and assets specified or disclosed under sub-section (3A), without the prior approval of the`
  line `Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal shall not grant such approval without giving notice to the applicant bank or`
  line `financial institution to show cause as to why approval prayed for should not be granted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that defendant shall be liable to account for the sale proceeds realised by sale of`
  line `secured assets in the ordinary course of business and deposit such sale proceeds in the account maintained`
  line `with the bank or financial institution holding security interest over such assets.]`
  line
  line `^13[(5) (i) the defendant shall within a period of thirty days from the date of service of summons,`
  line `present a written statement of his defence including claim for set-off under sub-section (6) or a`
  line
  line `counter-claim under sub-section (8), if any, and such written statement shall be accompanied with original`
  line `documents or true copies thereof with the leave of the Tribunal, relied on by the defendant in his defence:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the defendant fails to file the written statement within the said period of thirty`
  line `days, the Presiding Officer may, in exceptional cases and in special circumstances to be recorded in`
  line `writing, extend the said period by such further period not exceeding fifteen days to file the written`
  line `statement of his defence;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the defendant makes a disclosure of any property or asset pursuant to orders passed by the`
  line `Tribunal, the provisions of sub-section (4A) of this section shall apply to such property or asset;`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of non-compliance of any order made under clause (ii) of sub-section (4), the Presiding`
  line `Officer may, by an order, direct that the person or officer who is in default, be detained in civil prison for`
  line `a term not exceeding three months unless in the meantime the Presiding Officer directs his release:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Presiding Officer shall not pass an order under this clause without giving an`
  line `opportunity of being heard to such person or officer.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purpose of this section, the expression officer who is in default shall mean`
  line `such officer as defined in clause (60) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).]`
  line
  line `^14[(5A) On receipt of the written statement of defendant or on expiry of time granted by the Tribunal to`
  line `file the written statement, the Tribunal shall fix a date of hearing for admission or denial of documents`
  line `produced by the parties to the proceedings and also for continuation or vacation of the interim order`
  line `passed under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(5B) Where a defendant makes an admission of the full or part of the amount of debt due to a bank or`
  line `financial institution, the Tribunal shall order such defendant to pay the amount, to the extent of the`
  line `admission within a period of thirty days from the date of such order failing which the Tribunal may issue`
  line `a certificate in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (22) to the extent of the amount of debt due`
  line `admitted by the defendant.]`
  line
  line `(6) Where the defendant claims to set-off against the applicants demand any ascertained sum of`
  line `money legally recoverable by him from such applicant, the defendant may, at the first hearing of the`
  line `application, but not afterwards unless permitted by the Tribunal, present a written statement containing`
  line `the particulars of the debt ^15[the debt sought to be set-off along with original documents and other`
  line `evidence relied on in support of claim of set-off in relation to any ascertained sum of money, against the`
  line applicant.]
  line
  line `(7) The written statement shall have the same effect as a plaint in a cross-suit so as to enable the`
  line `Tribunal to pass a final order in respect both of the original claim and of the set-off.`
  line
  line `(8) A defendant in an application may, in addition to his right of pleading a set-off under`
  line `sub-section (6), set up, by way of counter-claim against the claim of the applicant, any right or claim in`
  line `respect of a cause of action accruing to the defendant against the applicant either before or after the filing`
  line `of the application but before the defendant has delivered his defence or before the time limited for`
  line `delivering his defence has expired, whether such counter-claim is in the nature of a claim for damages or`
  line not.
  line
  line `(9) A counter-claim under sub-section (8) shall have the same effect as a cross-suit so as to enable the`
  line `Tribunal to pass a final order on the same application, both on the original claim and on the`
  line counter-claim].
  line
  line `(10) The applicant shall be at liberty to file a written statement in answer to the counter-claim of the`
  line `defendant within such period ^16[as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^17[(10A) Every application under sub-section (3) or written statement of defendant under`
  line `sub-section (5) or claim of set-off under sub-section (6) or a counter-claim under sub-section (8) by the`
  line `defendant, or written statement by the applicant in reply to the counter-claim, under sub-section (10) or`
  line `any other pleading whatsoever, shall be supported by an affidavit sworn in by the applicant or defendant`
  line
  line `verifying all the facts and pleadings, the statements pleading documents and other documentary evidence`
  line `annexed to the application or written statement or reply to set-off or counter-claim, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that if there is any evidence of witnesses to be led by any party, the affidavits of such`
  line `witnesses shall be filed simultaneously by the party with the application or written statement or replies`
  line `filed under sub-section (10A).`
  line
  line `(10B) If any of the facts or pleadings in the application or written statement are not verified in the`
  line `manner provided under sub-section (10A), a party to the proceedings shall not be allowed to rely on such`
  line `facts or pleadings as evidence or any of the matters set out therein.]`
  line
  line `^18[(11) Where a defendant sets up a counter-claim in the written statement and in reply to such claim`
  line `the applicant contends that the claim thereby raised ought not to be disposed of by way of counter-claim`
  line `but in an independent action, the Tribunal shall decide such issue along with the claim of the applicant for`
  line `recovery of the debt.]`
  line
  line `^19* * * * *`
  line
  line `(13) (A) Where, at any stage of the proceedings, ^20[the Tribunal on an application made by the`
  line `applicant along with particulars of property to be attached and estimated value thereof, or otherwise is`
  line `satisfied], that the defendant, with intent to obstruct or delay or frustrate the execution of any order for the`
  line `recovery of debt that may be passed against him,--`
  line
  line `(i) is about to dispose of the whole or any part of his property; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is about to remove the whole or any part of his property from the local limits of the`
  line `jurisdiction of the Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(iii) is likely to cause any damage or mischief to the property or affect its value by misuse or`
  line `creating third party interest,`
  line `the Tribunal may direct the defendant, within a time to be fixed by it, either to furnish security, in such`
  line `sum as may be specified in the order, to produce and place at the disposal of the Tribunal, when required,`
  line `the said property or the value of the same, or such portion thereof as may be sufficient to satisfy the`
  line `certificate for the recovery of the debt, or to appear and show cause why he should not furnish security.`
  line
  line `(B) Where the defendant fails to show cause why he should not furnish security, or fails to furnish the`
  line `security required, within the time fixed by the Tribunal, the Tribunal may order the attachment of the`
  line `whole or such portion of the properties claimed by the applicant as the properties secured in his favour or`
  line `otherwise owned by the defendant as appears sufficient to satisfy any certificate for the recovery of debt.`
  line
  line `^21* * * * *`
  line
  line `(15) The Tribunal may also in the order direct the conditional attachment of the whole or any portion`
  line `of the property specified under ^22[sub-section (13).]`
  line
  line `(16) If an order of attachment is made without complying with the provisions of sub-section (13),`
  line `such attachment shall be void.`
  line
  line `(17) In the case of disobedience of an order made by the Tribunal under sub-sections (12), (13) and`
  line
  line `(18) or breach of any of the terms on which the order was made, the Tribunal may order the properties of`
  line `the person guilty of such disobedience or breach to be attached and may also order such person to be`
  line `detained in the civil prison for a term not exceeding three months, unless in the meantime the Tribunal`
  line `directs his release.`
  line
  line `(18) Where it appears to the Tribunal to be just and convenient, the Tribunal may, by order--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint a receiver of any property, whether before or after grant of certificate for recovery of`
  line debt;
  line
  line `(b) remove any person from the possession or custody of the property;`
  line
  line `(c) commit the same to the possession, custody or management of the receiver;`
  line
  line `(d) confer upon the receiver all such powers, as to bringing and defending suits in the courts or`
  line `filing and defending applications before the Tribunal and for the realisation, management, protection,`
  line `preservation and improvement of the property, the collection of the rents and profits thereof, the`
  line `application and disposal of such rents and profits, and the execution of documents as the owner`
  line `himself has, or such of those powers as the Tribunal thinks fit; and`
  line
  line `(e) appoint a Commissioner for preparation of an inventory of the properties of the defendant or`
  line `for the sale thereof.`
  line
  line `^23[(19) Where a certificate of recovery is issued against a company as defined under the Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) and such company is under liquidation, the Tribunal may by an order direct that`
  line `the sale proceeds of secured assets of such company be distributed in the same manner as provided in`
  line `section 326 of the Companies Act, 2013 or under any other law for the time being in force.]`
  line
  line `^24[(20) The Tribunal may, after giving the applicant and the defendant, an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `in respect of all claims, set-off or counter-claim, if any, and interest on such claims, within thirty days`
  line `from the date of conclusion of the hearings, pass interim or final order as it deems fit which may include`
  line `order for payment of interest from the date on which payment of the amount is found due up to the date of`
  line `realisation or actual payment.]`
  line
  line `^25[(20A) Where it is proved to the satisfaction of the Tribunal that the claim of the applicant has been`
  line `adjusted wholly or in part by any lawful agreement or compromise in writing and signed by the parties or`
  line `where the defendant has repaid or agreed to repay the claim of the applicant, the Tribunal shall pass`
  line `orders recording such agreement, compromise or satisfaction of the claim.]`
  line
  line `^26[(20AA) While passing the final order under sub-section (20), the Tribunal shall clearly specify the`
  line `assets of the borrower which security interest is created in favour of any bank or financial institution and`
  line `direct the Recovery Officers to distribute the sale proceeds of such assets as provided in`
  line `sub-section (20AB).`
  line
  line `(20AB) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law for the time being in force, the`
  line `proceeds from sale of secured assets shall be distributed in the following orders of priority, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the costs incurred for preservation and protection of secured assets, the costs of valuation,`
  line `public notice for possession and auction and other expenses for sale of assets shall be paid in full;`
  line
  line `(ii) debts owed to the bank or financial institution.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this sub-section, it is hereby clarified that on or after the`
  line `commencement of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), in cases where insolvency`
  line `and bankruptcy proceedings are pending in respect of secured assets of the borrower, the distribution of`
  line `proceeds from the sale of secured assets shall be subject to the order of priority as provided in that Code.]`
  line
  line `^27[(21) (i) The Tribunal shall send a copy of its final order and the recovery certificate, to the applicant`
  line `applicant and defendant.`
  line
  line `(ii) The applicant and the defendant may obtain copy of any order passed by the Tribunal on payment`
  line `on such fee as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^28[(22) The Presiding Officer shall issue a certificate of recovery along with the final order, under`
  line `sub-section (20), for payment of debt with interest under his signature to the Recovery Officer for`
  line `recovery of the amount of debt specified in the certificate.]`
  line
  line `^29[(22A) Any recovery certificate issued by the Presiding Officer under sub-section (22) shall be`
  line `deemed to be decree or order of the Court for the purposes of initiation of winding up proceedings against`
  line `a company registered under the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or Limited Liability Partnership`
  line `registered under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009) or insolvency proceedings`
  line `against any individual or partnership firm under any law for the time being in force, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `(23) Where the Tribunal, which has issued a certificate of recovery, is satisfied that the property is`
  line `situated within the local limits of the jurisdiction of two or more Tribunals, it may send the copies of the`
  line `certificate of recovery for execution to such other Tribunals where the property is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where the Tribunal to which the certificate of recovery is sent for execution`
  line `finds that it has no jurisdiction to comply with the certificate of recovery, it shall return the same to the`
  line `Tribunal which has issued it.`
  line
  line `(24) The application made to the Tribunal under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be dealt with`
  line `by it as expeditiously as possible and ^30[every effort shall be made by it to complete the proceedings in two`
  line `hearings, and to dispose of the application finally within one hundred and eighty days from the date of`
  line `receipt of the application.`
  line
  line `(25) The Tribunal may made such orders and give such directions as may be necessary or expedient`
  line `to give effect to its orders or to prevent abuse of its process or to secure the ends of justice.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 9, for section 19 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3 Clause (a) renumbered as clause (aa) thereof by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `4 Ins. by Act 30 of 2004, s. 20 (w.e.f. 11-11-2004).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 15 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `6 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `7 Ins. by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `8 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 15 (w.e.f. 15-5-2013).`
  line
  line `9 Sub-section (3A) renumbered as sub-section (3B) thereof by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `10 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `11 Ins. by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `12 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `13 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32, for sub-section (5A) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `14 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for "the dept sought to be set-off" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `15 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for "as may be fixed by the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `16 Ins. by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `17 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32, for sub-section (11) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `18 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for "the Tribunal is satisfied, by affidavit or otherwise" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `19. Omitted by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016)`
  line
  line `20 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sub-section (14) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `21 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32, for sub-section (19) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `22. Omitted by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016)`
  line `23 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sub-section (20) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `24 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 15 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `25 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `26 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sub-section (21) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `27 Subs. by s. 32, ibid., for sub-section (22) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `28 Ins. by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `29 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 32, for "endeavour shall be made by it" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_a:
  sectionId (5042)
  sectionNo 19A
  orderNo 23
  title `Filing of recovery applications, documents and written statements in electronic form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5042&sectionno=19A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[19A. Filing of recovery applications, documents and written statements in electronic`
  line `form.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, and without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions contained in section 6 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000), the Central`
  line `Government may by rules provide that from such date and before such Tribunal and Appellate Tribunal,`
  line `as may be notified,--`
  line
  line `(a) application or written statement or any other pleadings and the documents to be annexed`
  line `thereto required to be filed shall be submitted in the electronic form and authenticated with digital`
  line `signature of the applicant, defendant or any other petitioner in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(b) any summons, notice or communication or intimation as may be required to be served or`
  line `delivered under this Act, may be served or delivered by transmission of pleadings and documents by`
  line `electronic form and authenticated in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any interim or final order passed by the Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal displayed on the website`
  line `of such Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a public notice of such order and`
  line `transmission of such order by electronic mail to the registered address of the parties to the proceeding`
  line `shall be deemed to be served on such party.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may by rules provide that the electronic form for the purpose specified`
  line `in this section shall be exclusive, or in the alternative or in addition to the physical form, therefor.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal notified under sub-section (1), for the purpose of adopting`
  line `electronic filing, shall maintain its own website or common website with other Tribunals and Appellate`
  line `Tribunal or such other universally accessible repositories of electronic information and ensure that all`
  line `orders or directions issued by the Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal are displayed on the website of the`
  line `Tribunal or Appellate Tribunal, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) 'digital signature' means the digital signature as defined under clause (p) of section 2 of the`
  line `Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);`
  line
  line `(b) 'electronic form' with reference to an information or a document means the electronic form as`
  line `defined under clause (r) of section 2 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).]`
  line
  line `^*[19A. --The application made to Tribunal for exercising the powers of the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 shall be dealt with in the manner as provided under that`
  line Code..]
obj_root_law_sections_19_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `*.Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1-12-2019 in so far as it relates to personal guarantors to corporate debtors).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5043)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5043&sectionno=20&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in sub-section (2), any person`
  line `aggrieved by an order made, or deemed to have been made, by a Tribunal under this Act, may prefer an`
  line `appeal to an Appellate Tribunal having jurisdiction in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie to the Appellate Tribunal from an order made by a Tribunal with the consent of`
  line `the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of ^1[thirty days] from the date on`
  line `which a copy of the order made, or deemed to have been made, by the Tribunal is received by him and it`
  line `shall be in such form and be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `^1[thirty days] if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), ^2[ or under sub-section (1) of section 181 of the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016)] the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties`
  line `to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal and`
  line `to the concerned Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(6) The appeal filed before the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by it as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within six`
  line `months from the date of receipt of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 34, for "forty-five days" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 31 of 2016, s. 249 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 1-12-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5044)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Deposit of amount of debt due, on filing appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5044&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where an appeal is preferred by any person`
  line `from whom the amount of debt is due to a bank or a financial institution or a consortium of banks or`
  line `financial institutions, such appeal shall not be entertained by the Appellate Tribunal unless such person`
  line `has deposited with the Appellate Tribunal ^1[fifty per cent.] of the amount of debt so due from him as`
  line `determined by the Tribunal under section 19:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, ^2[reduce the amount`
  line `to be deposited by such amount which shall not be less than twenty-five per cent. of the amount of such`
  line `debt so due] to be deposited under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 35, for "seventy-five per cent". (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line `2 Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for "waive or reduce the amount" (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5045)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title `Procedure and powers of the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5045&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal and the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall not be bound the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this Act and of any rules, the Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall have powers to`
  line `regulate their own procedure including the places at which they shall have their sittings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging their`
  line `functions under this Act, the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any proceeding before the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for`
  line `all the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `^1[(4) For the purpose of proof of any entry in the 'bankers books', the provisions of the Bankers'`
  line `Books Evidence Act, 1891 (18 of 1891) shall apply to all the proceedings before the Tribunal or`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (5046)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 27
  title `Uniform procedure for conduct of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5046&sectionno=22A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Uniform procedure for conduct of proceedings. --The Central Government may, for the`
  line `purpose of this Act, by rules, lay down uniform procedure consistent with the provisions of this Act for`
  line `conducting the proceedings before the Tribunals and Appellate Tribunals.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5047)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 28
  title `Right to legal representation and Presenting Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5047&sectionno=23&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A bank or a financial institution`
  line `making an application to a Tribunal or an appeal to an Appellate Tribunal may authorise one or more`
  line `legal practitioners or any of its officers to act as Presenting Officers and every person so authorised by it`
  line `may present its case before the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The defendant may either appear in person or authorise one or more legal practitioners or any of`
  line `his or its officers to present his or its case before the Tribunal or the Appellate Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5048)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 29
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5048&sectionno=24&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to an application made to a Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5049)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 30
  title `Modes of recovery of debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes '```'
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5049&sectionno=25&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The Recovery Officer shall, on receipt of the copy of the`
  line `certificate under sub-section (7) of section 19, proceed to recover the amount of debt specified in the`
  line `certificate by one or more of the following modes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) attachment and sale of the movable or immovable property of the defendant;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) taking possession of property over which security interest is created or any other property`
  line `of the defendant and appointing receiver for such property and to sell the same;]`
  line
  line `(b) arrest of the defendant and his detention in prison;`
  line
  line `(c) appointing a receiver for the management of the movable or immovable properties of the`
  line defendant;
  line
  line `^1[(d) any other mode of recovery as may be prescribed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (5050)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 31
  title `Validity of certificate and amendment thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5050&sectionno=26&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall not be open to the defendant to`
  line `dispute before the Recovery Officer the correctness of the amount specified in the certificate, and no`
  line `objection to the certificate on any other ground shall also be entertained by the Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the issue of a certificate to a Recovery Officer, the Presiding Officer shall have`
  line `power to withdraw the certificate or correct any clerical or arithmetical mistake in the certificate by`
  line `sending intimation to the Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The Presiding Officer shall intimate to the Recovery Officer any order withdrawing or cancelling`
  line `a certificate or any correction made by him under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (5051)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 32
  title `Stay of proceedings under certificate and amendment or withdrawal thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5051&sectionno=27&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Notwithstanding that a certificate has been issued to the Recovery Officer for the`
  line `recovery of any amount, the Presiding Officer, may by an order, grant time for payment of the amount,`
  line `provided the defendant makes a down payment of not less than twenty-five per cent. of the amount`
  line `specified in the recovery certificate and gives an unconditional undertaking to pay the balance within a`
  line `reasonable time, which is acceptable to the applicant bank or financial institution holding recovery`
  line certificate.
  line
  line `(1A) The Recovery Officer shall, after receipt of the order passed under sub-section (1), stay the`
  line `proceedings until the expiry of the time so granted.`
  line
  line `(1B) Where defendant agrees to pay the amount specified in the Recovery Certificate and proceeding`
  line `are stayed by the Recovery Officer, the defendant shall forfeit right to file appeal against the orders of the`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(1C) Where the defendant commits any default in payment of the amount under sub-section (1), the`
  line `stay of recovery proceedings shall stand withdrawn and the Recovery Officer shall take steps for recovery`
  line `of remaining amount of debt due and payable.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where a certificate for the recovery of amount has been issued, the Presiding Officer shall keep`
  line `the Recovery Officer informed of any amount paid or time granted for payment, subsequent to the issue`
  line `of such certificate to the Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the order giving rise to a demand of amount for recovery of debt has been modified in`
  line `appeal, and, as a consequence thereof the demand is reduced, the Presiding Officer shall stay the recovery`
  line `of such part of the amount of the certificate as pertains to the said reduction for the period for which the`
  line `appeal remains pending.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a certificate for the recovery of debt has been received by the Recovery Officer and`
  line `subsequently the amount of the outstanding demands is reduced ^2[or enhanced] as a result of an appeal,`
  line `the Presiding Officer shall, when the order which was the subject matter of such appeal has become final`
  line `and conclusive, amend the certificate or withdraw it, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 10 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (5052)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 33
  title `Other modes of recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 11 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5052&sectionno=28&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a certificate has been issued to the Recovery Officer`
  line `under sub-section (7) of section 19, the Recovery Officer may, without prejudice to the modes of recovery`
  line `specified in section 25, recover the amount of debt by any one or more of the modes provided under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(2) If any amount is due from any person to the defendant, the Recovery Officer may require such`
  line `person to deduct from the said amount, the amount of debt due from the defendant under this Act and`
  line `such person shall comply with any such requisition and shall pay the sum so deducted to the credit of the`
  line `Recovery Officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any part of the amount exempt from`
  line `attachment in execution of a decree of a civil court under section 60 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(3) (i) The Recovery Officer may, at any time or from time to time, by notice in writing, require any`
  line `person from whom money is due or may become due to the defendant or to any person who holds or may`
  line `subsequently hold money for or on account of the defendant, to pay to the Recovery Officer either`
  line `forthwith upon the money becoming due or being held or within the time specified in the notice (not`
  line `being before the money becomes due or is held) so much of the money as is sufficient to pay the amount`
  line `of debt due from the defendant or the whole of the money when it is equal to or less than that amount.`
  line
  line `(ii) A notice under this sub-section may be issued to any person who holds or may subsequently hold`
  line `any money for or on account of the defendant jointly with any other person and for the purposes of this`
  line `sub-section, the shares of the joint holders in such amount shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved,`
  line `to be equal.`
  line
  line `(iii) A copy of the notice shall be forwarded to the defendant at his last address known to the`
  line `Recovery Officer and in the case of a joint account to all the joint holders at their last addresses known to`
  line `the Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(iv) Save as otherwise provided in this sub-section, every person to whom a notice is issued under this`
  line `sub-section shall be bound to comply with such notice, and, in particular, where any such notice is issued`
  line `to a post office, bank, financial institution, or an insurer, it shall not be necessary for any pass book,`
  line `deposit receipt, policy or any other document to be produced for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or`
  line `the like to be made before the payment is made notwithstanding any rule, practice or requirement to the`
  line contrary.
  line
  line `(v) Any claim respecting any property in relation to which a notice under this sub-section has been`
  line `issued arising after the date of the notice shall be void as against any demand contained in the notice.`
  line
  line `(vi) Where a person to whom a notice under this sub-section is sent objects to it by a statement on`
  line `oath that the sum demanded or the part thereof is not due to the defendant or that he does not hold any`
  line `money for or on account of the defendant, then, nothing contained in this sub-section shall be deemed to`
  line `require such person to pay any such sum or part thereof, as the case may be, but if it is discovered that`
  line `such statement was false in any material particular, such person shall be personally liable to the Recovery`
  line `Officer to the extent of his own liability to the defendant on the date of the notice, or to the extent of the`
  line `defendant’s liability for any sum due under this Act, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(vii) The Recovery Officer may, at any time or from time to time, amend or revoke any notice under`
  line `this sub-section or extend the time for making any payment in pursuance of such notice.`
  line
  line `(viii) The Recovery Officer shall grant a receipt for any amount paid in compliance with a notice`
  line `issued under this sub-section, and the person so paying shall be fully discharged from his liability to the`
  line `defendant to the extent of the amount so paid.`
  line
  line `(ix) Any person discharging any liability to the defendant after the receipt of a notice under this`
  line `sub-section shall be personally liable to the Recovery Officer to the extent of his own liability to the`
  line `defendant so discharged or to the extent of the defendants liability for any debt due under this Act,`
  line `whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(x) If the person to whom a notice under this sub-section is sent fails to make payment in pursuance`
  line `thereof to the Recovery Officer, he shall be deemed to be a defendant in default in respect of the amount`
  line `specified in the notice and further proceedings may be taken against him for the realisation of the amount`
  line `as if it were a debt due from him, in the manner provided in sections 25, 26 and 27 and the notice shall`
  line `have the same effect as an attachment of a debt by the Recovery Officer in exercise of his powers under`
  line `section 25.`
  line
  line `(4) The Recovery Officer may apply to the court in whose custody there is money belonging to the`
  line `defendant for payment to him of the entire amount of such money, or if it is more than the amount of debt`
  line `due, an amount sufficient to discharge the amount of debt so due.`
  line
  line `^1[(4A) The Recovery Officer may, by order, at any stage of the execution of the certificate of`
  line `recovery, require any person, and in case of a company, any of its officers against whom or which the`
  line `certificate of recovery is issued, to declare on affidavit the particulars of his or its assets.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Recovery Officer may recover any amount of debt due from the defendant by distraint and`
  line `sale of his movable property in the manner laid down in the Third Schedule to the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (5053)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 34
  title `Application of certain provisions of Income-tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5053&sectionno=29&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Second and Third`
  line `Schedules to the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules,`
  line `1962, as in force from time to time shall, as far as possible, apply with necessary modifications as if the`
  line `said provisions and the rules referred to the amount of debt due under this Act instead of to the`
  line `Income-tax:`
  line
  line `Provided that any reference under the said provisions and the rules to the assessee shall be`
  line `construed as a reference to the defendant under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (5054)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 35
  title `Appeal against the order of Recovery Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 30 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5054&sectionno=30&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Appeal against the order of Recovery Officer.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 29, any person aggrieved by an order of the Recovery Officer made under this Act may, within`
  line `thirty days from the date on which a copy of the order is issued to him, prefer an appeal to the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Tribunal may, after giving an opportunity to the`
  line `appellant to be heard, and after making such inquiry as it deems fit, confirm, modify or set aside the order`
  line `made by the Recovery Officer in exercise of his powers under sections 25 to 28 (both inclusive).]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (5055)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 36
  title `Deposit of amount of debt due for filing appeal against orders of the Recovery Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5055&sectionno=30A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Deposit of amount of debt due for filing appeal against orders of the Recovery`
  line `Officer. -- Where an appeal is preferred against any order of the Recovery Officer, under section 30, by`
  line `any person from whom the amount of debt is due to a bank or financial institution or consortium of banks`
  line `or financial institutions, such appeal shall not be entertained by the Tribunal unless such person has`
  line `deposited with the Tribunal fifty per cent. of the amount of debt due as determined by the Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (5056)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 37
  title `Transfer of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5056&sectionno=31&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every suit or other proceeding pending before any court`
  line `immediately before the date of establishment of a Tribunal under this Act, being a suit or proceeding the`
  line `cause of action whereon it is based is such that it would have been, if it had arisen after such`
  line `establishment, within the jurisdiction of such Tribunal, shall stand transferred on that date to such`
  line `Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any appeal pending as aforesaid before any`
  line `court:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that any recovery proceedings in relation to the recovery of debts due to any`
  line `multi-State co-operative bank pending before the date of commencement of the Enforcement of Security`
  line `Interest and Recovery of Debts Laws (Amendment) Act, 2012 (1 of 2013) under the Multi-State`
  line `Co-operative Societies Act, 2002 (39 of 2002), shall be continued and nothing contained in this section`
  line `shall apply to such proceedings.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where any suit or other proceeding stands transferred from any court to a Tribunal under`
  line `sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the court shall, as soon as may be after such transfer, forward the records of such suit or other`
  line `proceeding to the Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Tribunal may, on receipt of such records, proceed to deal with such suit or other`
  line `proceeding, so far as may be, in the same manner as in the case of an application made under`
  line `section 19 from the stage which was reached before such transfer or from any earlier stage ^2*** as the`
  line `Tribunal may deed fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 16 (w.e.f. 15-1-2013).`
  line
  line `2. The words "de novo" omitted by Act 1 of 2000, s. 13 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (5057)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of Tribunal to issue certificate of recovery in case of decree or order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5057&sectionno=31A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Power of Tribunal to issue certificate of recovery in case of decree or order.-- (1) Where a`
  line `decree or order was passed by any court before the commencement of the Recovery of Debts Due to`
  line `Banks and Financial Institutions (Amendment) Act, 2000 (1 of 2000) and has not yet been executed, then,`
  line `the decree-holder may apply to the Tribunal to pass an order for recovery of the amount.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Tribunal may issue a certificate for`
  line `recovery to a Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of a certificate under sub-section (2), the Recovery Officer shall proceed to recover the`
  line `amount as if it was a certificate in respect of a debt recoverable under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_b:
  sectionId (5058)
  sectionNo 31B
  orderNo 39
  title `Priority to secured creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5058&sectionno=31B&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_31_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[31B. Priority to secured creditors.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, the rights of secured creditors to realise secured debts due and payable to them by`
  line `sale of assets over which security interest is created, shall have priority and shall be paid in priority over`
  line `all other debts and Government dues including revenues, taxes, cesses and rates due to the Central`
  line `Government, State Government or local authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, it is hereby clarified that on or after the`
  line `commencement of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), in cases where insolvency or`
  line `bankruptcy proceedings are pending in respect of secured assets of the borrower, priority to secured`
  line `creditors in payment of debt shall be subject to the provisions of that Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (5059)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 40
  title `Chairperson, Presiding Officer and staff of Appellate Tribunal and Tribunal to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 15, for section 32 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5059&sectionno=32&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[32. Chairperson, Presiding Officer and staff of Appellate Tribunal and Tribunal to be public`
  line `servants.-- The Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal, the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal, the Recovery`
  line `Officer and other officers and employees of an Appellate Tribunal and a Tribunal shall be deemed to be`
  line `public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (5060)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 41
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or of an Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5060&sectionno=33&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or against ^1[the Presiding Officer of a Tribunal or the Chairperson of an Appellate Tribunal] or against the Recovery Officer for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (5061)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 42
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 16, for "and the Sick Industrial Companies (Special Provisions) Act, 1985" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5061&sectionno=34&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided under sub-section (2), the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder shall be in addition to, and not in`
  line `derogation of, the Industrial Finance Corporation Act, 1948 (15 of 1948), the State Financial Corporations`
  line `Act, 1951 (63 of 1951), the Unit Trust of India Act, 1963 (52 of 1963), the Industrial Reconstruction`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1984 (62 of 1984),`
  line `^1[the Sick Industrial Companies (Special Provisions) Act, 1985`
  line `(1 of 1986) and the Small Industries Development Bank of India Act, 1989 (39 of 1989).]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (5062)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5062&sectionno=35&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of the period of three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (5063)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5063&sectionno=36&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may, provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) other business or commercial rights of similar nature under clause (jb) of section 2;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa)] the salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of ^4[the`
  line `Chairpersons, the Presiding Officers, Recovery Officers and other officers and employees of the`
  line `Tribunal and the Appellate Tribunal] under sections 7, 12 and 13;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for the investigation of misbehaviour or incapacity of ^3[the Chairpersons of`
  line `Appellate Tribunals and the Presiding Officers of the Tribunals], under sub-section (3) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which an application may be made under section 19, the documents and other`
  line `evidence by which such application shall be accompanied and the fees payable in respect of the filing`
  line `of such application;`
  line
  line `^4[(ca) the form of application and the fee for filing application under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 19;]`
  line
  line `^5[(cc) the rate of fee to be refunded to the applicant under sub-section ^85`
  line `(3B) of section 19 of the`
  line `the Act;]`
  line
  line `^6[(cca) the period for filing written statement under sub-section (10) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(ccb) the fee for obtaining copy of the order of the Tribunal under sub-section (21) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(ccc) the form and manner of authenticating digital signature under clause (a), and the manner of`
  line `authenticating service or delivery of pleadings and documents under clause (b), of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 19A;`
  line
  line `(ccd) the form and manner of filing application and other documents in the electronic form under`
  line `sub-section (1) and manner of display of orders of the Tribunal and Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 19A;]`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which an appeal may be filed before the Appellate Tribunal under section 20 and`
  line `the fees payable in respect of such appeal;`
  line
  line `^7[(da) the rules of uniform procedure for conducting the proceedings before the Tribunals and`
  line `Appellate Tribunals under section 22A;`
  line
  line `(db) the other mode of recovery under clause (d) of section 25;]`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^8[(3) Every notification issued under sub-section (4) of section 1, section 3 and section 8 and every`
  line `rule made by the Central Government under this Act, shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification or rule or both Houses agree that the notification or rule should not be`
  line `issued or made, the notification or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that notification or rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `2 Clause (a) numbered as clause (aa) thereof by s. 42, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 17, for "the Presiding Officers" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "the Presiding Officers of the Tribunals and Appellate Tribunals" (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `5 Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 42 (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `6 Ins. by Act 1 of 2013, s. 17 (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
  line
  line `7 Subs. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 42, for (3A) (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  line
  line `8 Subs. by Act 1 of 2000, s. 17, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 17-1-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (5064)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493&sectionId=5064&sectionno=37&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_33_00045_199351_1524048948493
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions`
  line `Ordinance, 1993 (Ord. 25 of 1993) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
